12:58.660 --> 13:04.840
Many of the passages in the book describe hallucinations and illusions so realistically that the reader might assume Dick had first had experience.

13:05.620 --> 13:10.860
We asked Williams if it is true that Dick had never used hallucinogens before he wrote the three-stigmata of Palmer Eldritch.

13:10.860 --> 13:18.740
We also asked him to comment on the report that in the aftermath of his experiments with psychedelics, Dick was afraid to read the proofs of the three-stigmata of Palmer Eldritch.

13:42.080 --> 13:53.320
Then taking LSD and reading the galleys, that's possibly true except that it was years before he read the galleys and maybe years before he took the trip also.

13:53.820 --> 14:01.800
But he was afraid of it before he read them. He always claimed anyway to be scared to read the galleys when they sent them to him.

14:03.240 --> 14:11.160
And he didn't finally re-read them up again according to what he always claimed until a number of years later.

14:14.520 --> 14:19.800
But I'm sure there's no question that it scared him. It scared him while he wrote it.

14:19.800 --> 14:38.800
At one point he told an interviewer that he wrote it to kind of exercise a terrifying vision of the man with the stigmata that he was seeing in the sky while driving to the shack on the California coast that he was doing his writing in.

14:39.420 --> 14:49.400
And it was very real to him and terrifying while he was writing his songs while reading it. I think by the way that it's a brilliant novel.

14:59.980 --> 15:01.180
The Man in the High Castle

15:01.180 --> 15:09.120
The Man in the High Castle is presently considered to be Dick's major accomplishment. It's an alternate world novel which describes the United States in the aftermath of the Axis powers winning World War II.

15:09.300 --> 15:16.660
A side light is that characters in the book learn that in an alternate world the allies have won. They learn this through the Yi Qing, the Chinese book of changes.

15:17.080 --> 15:23.860
It has been reported that for a period Dick himself consulted the Yi Qing but that he repudiated it. We asked Williams if this is true.

15:49.320 --> 16:03.980
The book, the oracle, essentially told him next stop that it wasn't useful for him to keep asking questions of it. His feeling and what he said was that it was actually trying to steer him.

16:05.740 --> 16:22.800
It's some wrong fashion but I think that that kind of incidental effect of The Man in the High Castle is introducing the Chinese book of changes to so many people who have been introduced into the whole culture. It's very fascinating.

